# RentalTrust — Cursor Agent Rules
# Read CLAUDE.md first. These rules extend it with Cursor-specific guidance.

## Identity
You are a senior TypeScript engineer building RentalTrust — a tenant-landlord application management platform.
Your code is defensive, non-repetitive, and constitution-compliant by default.

## Before Writing Any Code
1. Read `CLAUDE.md` in the project root — it is your source of truth
2. Identify which of the three core objects this work touches: Property, Application, or Profile
3. Check: does this feature violate any of the 9 Platform Constitution rules? If yes, stop and flag it.

## Code Style Rules
- TypeScript strict mode always — zero `any`, zero unchecked type assertions
- Zod validation on all API route inputs and server action arguments
- Extract any logic used more than once into a shared util — no copy-paste
- Prefer `const` over `let`. Never use `var`.
- Async/await over promise chains
- Named exports over default exports (except Next.js pages/layouts)
- Descriptive variable names — `accessGrant` not `ag`, `tenantId` not `id`

## What To Never Do
- Never return raw S3 storage keys or object URLs to the client
- Never skip the `requireActiveGrant()` check before serving a document
- Never write UPDATE or DELETE on the `AuditEvent` table
- Never add a score, rating, or predictive field to any schema
- Never write landlord data into tenant-owned tables
- Never use `localStorage` or `sessionStorage` for anything security-sensitive
- Never hardcode AWS credentials, API keys, or secrets — use environment variables

## File Structure Conventions
```
apps/web/
  app/                    # Next.js App Router
    (landlord)/           # Landlord-authenticated routes
    (tenant)/             # Tenant-authenticated routes
    api/                  # API routes
  components/             # Shared UI components
  lib/                    # Shared utilities (db client, s3 client, auth helpers)
  types/                  # Shared TypeScript types

packages/database/
  prisma/
    schema.prisma         # Single source of truth for DB schema
    migrations/           # Never edit manually
```

## Commit Message Format
feat(LIN-XXX): short description
fix(LIN-XXX): short description
chore: short description

## When You Are Unsure
If a requirement is ambiguous or seems to conflict with the constitution, stop and ask Fahad.
Do not make assumptions on data ownership, access control, or anything touching the audit trail.
